Ok, strangely enough, it actually has nothing to do with the nested classes (the following code causes the same crash):
```scala
class MyClass {
  
  var foo = false;
  var bar = false;
  
  def getBlah: String = {
    try {
      if (foo) {
	return null; // must be null
      }
      "blah";
    } finally {
      if (bar) {
	println("hello"); // do anything here
      }
    }
  }
  
}
```
